8eed465e-9203-406b-b52c-75ded68ec11c.text:
Term: New York City
Definition: The most populous city in the United States, located at the southern tip of New York State, and the largest metropolitan area in the U.S. by both population and urban area.

bacb87ab-6e35-4697-a98e-e9979a0cc078.text:
Term: boroughs
Definition: Five administrative divisions of New York City, each coextensive with a respective county of the state of New York: Brooklyn, Queens, Manhattan, The Bronx, and Staten Island.

a3bfebcc-ef75-4673-97be-642b59cc595e.text:
Term: metropolitan statistical area
Definition: A geographical region with a relatively high population density at its core and close economic ties throughout the area.

fad92868-a3bf-4a73-a759-45cedb206488.text:
Term: combined statistical area
Definition: A combination of adjacent metropolitan and micropolitan statistical areas in the United States and Puerto Rico that can demonstrate economic or social linkage.

8530adcf-796c-425b-a76e-9b52a36ae8ee.text:
Term: megacities
Definition: A city with a population of over 10 million people.

1096b66a-8ef6-460a-a8f1-3af72327c01b.text:
Term: United Nations
Definition: An intergovernmental organization that aims to maintain international peace and security, develop friendly relations among nations, achieve international cooperation, and be a center for harmonizing the actions of nations.

c369f8c5-7329-4f6b-8731-0e246a7d2a37.text:
Term: Pulitzer Prizes
Definition: A series of annual awards for achievements in journalism, literature, and musical composition in the United States.

9dbe2dbd-d25c-4410-8898-f20a88dc9f56.text:
Term: Times Square
Definition: A major commercial and tourist destination in Manhattan, New York City.

d2fc923c-cc5c-4f92-b391-1287ceec2380.text:
Term: New Netherland
Definition: A Dutch colony in North America that existed from 1614 until 1664.

77610d48-1dad-42d0-aab9-aacb4a1c0331.text:
Term: Dutch West India Company
Definition: A Dutch trading company that operated as a monopoly in New Netherland from 1621 until 1639-1640.

a14ce5d1-ad91-4bfd-9980-2a72a1e6dfa7.text:
Term: patroon system
Definition: A system instituted by the Dutch to attract settlers to New Netherland, whereby wealthy Dutchmen who brought 50 colonists would be awarded land and local political autonomy.

0871b38e-6dd7-4609-bd88-2c8a7c7bb931.text:
Term: Peter Stuyvesant
Definition: The last Director-General of New Netherland, who served from 1647 until 1664.

705f9057-5fb2-4dbd-a571-2d2d3165f45e.text:
Term: Treaty of Breda
Definition: A treaty signed in 1667 between the Dutch and English that resulted in the Dutch keeping Suriname and the English keeping New Amsterdam (which was renamed New York).

947a0668-2521-4ad6-b9c2-16df0083e423.text:
Term: African Burying Ground
Definition: A cemetery discovered in Foley Square in the 1990s that included 10,000 to 20,000 graves of colonial-era Africans, some enslaved and some free.

3dff9c02-6787-4b79-8e50-9055144e8c22.text:
Term: Stamp Act Congress
Definition: A meeting held in New York in 1765 in response to the Stamp Act, which imposed taxes on printed materials in the American colonies.

cf256dba-9d97-4899-8838-6fe6f4fa1077.text:
Term: Battle of Long Island
Definition: The largest battle of the American Revolutionary War, fought on August 27, 1776, in Brooklyn, New York City.

176ae083-05d4-4b85-993b-fbce65c5e919.text:
Term: New York Police Department
Definition: The police force of New York City.

fef16cd2-8c18-418f-a5fe-0b5664aca5df.text:
Term: Irish immigrants
Definition: People who immigrated to the United States from Ireland.

87a39556-27af-4094-b328-c4ec8d0d375d.text:
Term: lynched
Definition: To kill someone, especially by hanging, without a legal trial.

e4f69021-0943-4bcd-869a-a1ae1c5b210d.text:
Term: civil unrest
Definition: A situation in which people in a country are angry and likely to protest or fight.

4fbe3c6e-8f0c-410f-a928-57be4b858195.text:
Term: megacity
Definition: A very large city, typically one with a population of over ten million people.

6657882a-8e86-4068-8dd0-ec45f46f58b4.text:
Term: World Trade Center
Definition: A complex of buildings in Lower Manhattan, New York City, that were destroyed in the September 11 attacks.

96ccadef-3499-4f9e-97d7-c76f21902929.text:
Term: COVID-19
Definition: A highly infectious respiratory illness caused by the SARS-CoV-2 virus.

6288238a-2168-4dd6-9b99-30ffb002662f.text:
Term: monkeypox outbreak
Definition: An outbreak of a viral disease similar to smallpox, which occurred in the LGBT community in New York City in 2022.

dae35ec8-7d1e-4845-b0f1-b137c458a4fe.text:
Term: Hudson River
Definition: A river in the northeastern United States, flowing from the Adirondack Mountains in New York into the Atlantic Ocean.

bd8c8cfe-aa35-4856-afbd-a74ffc49b477.text:
Term: estuary
Definition: A partly enclosed coastal body of brackish water with one or more rivers or streams flowing into it, and with a free connection to the open sea.

6b136d22-9963-4c63-af87-e04c947c4e9c.text:
Term: East River
Definition: A tidal strait in New York City.

05ed0c3c-44bc-465a-ab88-ecccd3daddca.text:
Term: Five Boroughs
Definition: Refers to the five counties that make up New York City: Bronx, Brooklyn, Manhattan, Queens, and Staten Island.

cd22749b-5f04-4fdf-b6da-174e7fa53468.text:
Term: Staten Island
Definition: The most suburban of the five boroughs, located southwest of Manhattan and connected to it by the free Staten Island Ferry.

60bcd328-f7a1-461b-90a8-8b38d71ae220.text:
Term: Todt Hill
Definition: The highest point on the eastern seaboard south of Maine, located on Staten Island.

53dfe654-a811-492e-8ef3-cbd0e8ef2d48.text:
Term: Manhattan
Definition: The geographically smallest and most densely populated borough of New York City, known for its skyscrapers, Central Park, and cultural, administrative, and financial centers.

8eb6d0fc-26c5-41f4-96b7-98a42483f5c1.text:
Term: Brooklyn
Definition: The most populous borough of New York City, located on the western tip of Long Island and known for its cultural diversity, independent art scene, and distinctive neighborhoods.

5bcaa6fe-d218-42da-b713-f7ce1f2bd8de.text:
Term: Queens
Definition: The largest borough of New York City, located on Long Island north and east of Brooklyn, and known for its ethnic diversity, commercial and residential prominence, and hosting of the annual U.S. Open tennis tournament.

bfeb2cc3-2570-4f41-8fba-16b216157592.text:
Term: The Bronx
Definition: The northernmost borough of New York
